        <script data-cfasync="false" src="/cdn-cgi/scripts/5c5dd728/cloudflare-static/email-decode.min.js"></script><script type='application/json' id="_INITIAL_REACT_PROPS_">
    {"corporatePage":{"errors":null,"redirectUrl":null},"reduxData":{"alerts":[],"brandedBanner":{"content":"[PRO SALE: Get 50% off annual Pro memberships | __USE CODE FEB50__](https://www.codecademy.com/subscriptions/proAnnualV4a/checkout?periods=year\u0026discountCode=FEB50)","backgroundColor":"navy","id":"3R0xRQAOeucL97mFJNWQkz"},"contentful":{"homepage":{"id":"1qyjZlCFo9LLw640COQQvy","content_type":"homepage","name":"Homepage","hero_title":"Join the millions learning to code with Codecademy for free","learner_stories":{"id":"1B2bHslKdHg2GTFHAeiUAr","content_type":"section","internal_title":"Homepage Stories","heading":"Stories from real people","description":"Watch and read stories from the Codecademy community.","refs":[{"id":"2MO8kzxJNYEMAMnzkobseL","content_type":"learnerStory","story_title":"Taking a different path: One Team Lead's story","story_type":"software-engineering","first_name":"Giacomo","last_name":"S.","country":"England","city":"London","portrait":"//images.ctfassets.net/go6kr6r0ykrq/1HRZqDGLeXXKvgDDvCLMtb/d93f59bd74c075a79788a0c46335553c/GiacomoSorbi.jpeg","short_quote":"That just opened the tap of dopamine in my brain.","long_quote":"Also, when you’re able to teach somebody else, it means you’re able to put yourself in someone else’s shoes and explain a concept in basic terms, that is what allows you to gain full mastery.         ","occupation":"Team Lead","learner_type":["Career Switcher"],"domain_types":["web-development","machine-learning","javascript","html-css"],"reviewed_by_marketing":true,"question_answers":[{"id":"1kpC3haQow3oKQzFxPcKdS","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"intro_section_Giacomo","description":"As a contractor, Giacomo has worked for companies like Facebook, Deutsche Bank, BP, and Toptal."},{"id":"7womoSW0LTrYE8i09HB4hh","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"inspire_question_Giacomo","title":"What inspired you to code?","description":"In school, I studied marketing and finance, then went more into marketing.\n\nMy main turning point was when a marketing client called me, very angry, because their site wasn’t working. The previous developers updated components using some JavaScript code, which was obsolete. \n\nI figured out how to fix it almost on my own. That just opened the tap of dopamine in my brain. I liked the sense of fulfillment. \n\nFrom there, I spent my spare time training myself mostly on Codecademy when it started. I've run the Codecademy London Meetup for the past six years.\n"},{"id":"12hqTxX5SGkaWRfvIQa2pJ","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"memorable_projects_Giacomo","title":"What are your most memorable projects?","description":"The first project you architect is like your creature. You like to see it grow much like it is your child.\n\nWorking for Facebook was also cool because you’re surrounded by people who have managed to clear a higher bar. Most of them have Computer Science degrees, and I studied business. \n\nBeing there and being able to hold my ground, pass the interview, perform, and deliver — that was refreshing.\n"},{"id":"24Wdv5RIwDWVSskNJfbGJr","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"advice_question_Giacomo","title":"Any advice for those who are new to coding?","description":"My suggestion would be give it a shot, and then give it some more shots. \n\nIf you’re not successful, it’s not necessarily you. It might not be the right resource, or it might not be what makes you tick. \n\nAlso, when you can teach somebody else, it means you’re able to put yourself in someone else’s shoes and explain a concept in basic terms. That is what allows you to gain full mastery. \n"},{"id":"40F19Cw9XSgfJIHKpPSrMD","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"fun_question_Giacomo","title":"When you’re not coding, what do you do for fun?","description":"I enjoy coding for leisure, which is very different from what you do for work. You can explore and fiddle with technologies you wouldn’t in a business environment. \n\nI also like urban hiking. It helps me think better. \n\nOne of the things I’ve learned as an Engineer is how you manage and master your focus. You learn that bashing your head against your monitor to try to find a solution is very rarely helpful.\n"}],"related_content":[{"id":"2etqdfBumQexwSLCivWFKj","content_type":"contentReference","type":"category","slug":"web-development"},{"id":"7XZceOk7HsZde5UwaFRC6","content_type":"contentReference","type":"category","slug":"javascript"},{"id":"7mklK5MRZwcIFtW4hwDAKn","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"machine-learning"},{"id":"5jQ0BLezzb20G45MSGeWuw","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"learn-c-plus-plus"}]},{"id":"41NQvA0QQfkxGz5SIWRoc9","content_type":"learnerStory","story_title":"See how this Architect switched to UX Design","story_type":"web-development","first_name":"Alison","last_name":"V.","country":"United States","city":"Columbus","portrait":"//images.ctfassets.net/go6kr6r0ykrq/7EnAeoXDH50HmJG1BVJHFs/d8a3620dd34a336c2e1464d677b9052b/AlisonVoghel.jpg","short_quote":"Pick one thing, and really learn it.","long_quote":"It can be a lot like drinking from a fire hose where you’re trying to do everything at once. What worked for me was to learn HTML and then build a website using only that, just to see what I could do with it.","occupation":"Senior UX Designer","company":"Acquia","learner_type":["Career Switcher"],"domain_types":["html-css"],"reviewed_by_marketing":true,"question_answers":[{"id":"2oWxsuxtoktaNYmG4QmiEE","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"inspire_question_Alison","title":"What inspired you to learn to code? ","description":"After I got my master's degree, I started working at an architecture firm. It was not what I anticipated. I felt like I wasn’t getting to be creative or technical. \n\nI had just moved to Chicago for my job and ended up getting laid off right when the pandemic hit. \n\nI thought this was a good opportunity to take a step back and see what it was that I was missing from my career. That’s when I really went all-in on Codecademy. \n"},{"id":"12hhTtO6SUjGmj2T9JqgCb","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"impact_question_Alison","title":"How has learning to code impacted you?","description":"It has definitely increased my confidence in my abilities. \n\nI don’t use every coding language I’ve learned on every project, but I have more confidence to say, “These are the things I did, here are my certificates, these are the projects I’ve done,” and that adds to my design background.\n\nChanging to a different career can be pretty daunting, but to be able to back up my skills with those concrete things definitely helped me. \n"},{"id":"6p3KWX3dLMF6R8AXRpUt5u","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"dreamproject_question_Alison","title":"Describe your dream project.","description":"Design systems — that’s not just because that’s what I’m currently working on. I just got lucky that’s what needed to be worked on when I joined my current team. \n\nI really like working on, building out, and increasing the usability of a design system. \n"},{"id":"5wmNtpbYpUguNmk7h3wRGx","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"advice_question_Alison","title":"Any advice for those who are new to coding?","description":"Pick one thing, and really learn it. Really get into it and feel confident in it before trying to then take on another thing. \n\nIt can be a lot like drinking from a fire hose where you’re trying to do everything at once. What worked for me was to learn HTML and then build a website using only that, just to see what I could do with it. \n"},{"id":"2BNDlWhlJn20BzOBqAZCAu","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"fun_question_Alison","title":"When not coding, what do you do for fun?","description":"I just bought a house, and — having an architecture background — I’m really excited. That’s what my free time will be, making updates to my house. \n"}],"related_content":[{"id":"3MqTtNQOcXuPTXE1XBZjl","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"learn-bootstrap"},{"id":"2hvB9u4GOLWy2Xiaf6jLTF","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"react-101"},{"id":"3eJrGvpyu19gVk3AMG9nBE","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"learn-html"}]},{"id":"6PXY3ugBEw8MV5YffXH6sp","content_type":"learnerStory","story_title":"Lessons from a Chef turned Deputy CTO","story_type":"software-engineering","first_name":"Manuel","last_name":"S.","country":"Belgium","city":"Brussels","portrait":"//images.ctfassets.net/go6kr6r0ykrq/PsoQ94ZyA6wDGnzSr4CjF/f94e1023dc2fd8a146b1bcccc72879e6/ManuelSousa.jpg","short_quote":"I like coding because of the mental challenge.","long_quote":"It’s really interesting how tech can touch all these things. Personally, for me, it’s mind-expanding.                                                                                                   ","occupation":"Deputy CTO","company":"PaxFamilia","learner_type":["Career Switcher"],"domain_types":["html-css","ruby","code-foundations"],"reviewed_by_marketing":true,"question_answers":[{"id":"3n0ELnAPPBDQfFhm2RAIha","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"inspire_question_Manuel","title":"What inspired you to learn to code?","description":"I studied economics at my university, but it was a thing my parents recommended. I really hated it, so I dropped out. Eventually, I went into cooking and was a professional chef for 3–4 years. \n\nMy brother is a tour guide, and a tourist did bootcamps. He mentioned this, and it inspired me. That’s when I got the money together to do one. I started Codecademy to prepare for it.\n\nBecause I was so new to coding, and because the bootcamp was going to speed through front-end topics like CSS and HTML, I used Codecademy for that.\n"},{"id":"7mudDwlaW409VVN52ux6LG","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"impact_question_Manuel","title":"How has coding impacted your life?","description":"I liked cooking — but I like coding because of the mental challenge.\n\nI’m a deputy CTO, so I don’t just code anymore. I do a lot of communication between different interests in my company — with people who may not have a technical understanding of the codebase, with juniors that are lost, with bigger clients, and stuff like that. \n\nIt’s really interesting how tech can touch all these things. Personally, for me, it’s mind-expanding. \n"},{"id":"1ycsMRRtfLCFDWjHOfaAkY","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"dreamproject_question_Manuel","title":"Describe your dream project.","description":"Neuralink from Elon Musk. I’ve been looking at the careers page for a long time. I like Elon Musk — his message and why he set the company up. \n\nIt seems like it would be versatile work, where I’d constantly be learning or becoming multidisciplinary. \n"},{"id":"I16ZaCyW9ermc52OS6bzX","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"advice_question_Manuel","title":"Any advice for those who are new to coding?","description":"You need to be patient. I think everybody says this, but there’s no easy pill. You need to be able to fail and not be discouraged by failing. \n"},{"id":"3yDhTd5WIHc9fWNPz6vkBO","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"fun_question_Manuel","title":"When you're not working, what do you do for fun?","description":"Mostly, I like socializing because it can be quite intensive to sit working on something logical all day. \n\nYou need to balance it out. I did not do that in the beginning. I was all-in on consolidating this career shift, but I wouldn't recommend it. \n\nNow, I have a much more healthy balance. In some ways, that’s made it even better at work because I’m more charged and better able to make decisions. \n"}],"related_content":[{"id":"1d0HlNfoZPHilNLWXJnrbx","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"learn-ruby"},{"id":"3eJrGvpyu19gVk3AMG9nBE","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"learn-html"},{"id":"7yYK7WBGgZxnmAU2bum7yt","content_type":"contentReference","type":"path","slug":"learn-how-to-build-websites"},{"id":"4DCoszcEfiTMmNI4s9WjyQ","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"learn-git"}]},{"id":"5QNjwhzuCwfMfSPezJhWra","content_type":"learnerStory","story_title":"How one Developer learned to code with her disability","story_type":"web-development","first_name":"Rosita","last_name":"R.","country":"Netherlands","city":"Brummen","portrait":"//images.ctfassets.net/go6kr6r0ykrq/3ObHLUqjmfzpkrQLuMzF2n/ec9ad9ff4f6cea017a3057c8336eec3f/Rosita.jpg","short_quote":"I always needed help if something had to be fixed, and I wanted to do it myself.","long_quote":"I work with the government to help other people with disabilities find jobs. We give workshops to employers and to disabled people without jobs. We show them what they need on their resume or how to apply.","occupation":"Front-End Developer","learner_type":["Career Upgrader"],"domain_types":["code-foundations","html-css"],"reviewed_by_marketing":true,"question_answers":[{"id":"52HUAhvRw1kOySXWpkD3Or","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"intro_question_Rosita","description":"Rosita originally [shared her story on our blog ](https://www.codecademy.com/resources/blog/learning-to-code-with-my-disability/ \"Rosita's story\")in January 2021. We caught up with her to see how she’s progressed since then."},{"id":"6X6DIfRvqy58g6dzG69Rp6","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"inspire_question_Rosita","title":"What inspired you to learn to code? ","description":"I started my WordPress blog a few years ago. Back then, you had to know some code. I didn't want to install a plugin just to add an attribute to a link. \n\nI always needed help if something had to be fixed, and I wanted to do it myself. Someone suggested that I should learn HTML and CSS, so I did, and I started at Codecademy in 2017.\n\nIn March 2020, I really wanted to become a Developer, so I had to really learn. Because of COVID-19, everything was closed, so I paid for Codecademy Pro. I feel like it’s a much better way to learn because you have Career Paths and Skill Paths you can follow. \n"},{"id":"5FrBmnaenNjU0Qs3txg5g","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"impact_question_Rosita","title":"How has coding impacted your life?","description":"Previously, I was a stay-at-home mom. Except for raising my son, I didn’t have a goal in my life. Now, I am a Front-End Developer and participating in society."},{"id":"769ElrNrERxLKa88v3xv4H","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"dreamproject_question_Rosita","title":"Describe your dream project. ","description":"Something with accessibility. Everyone should be able to use the internet. \n\nI would really like to see accessibility become normal for all developers so that all websites and software will be accessible to all. "},{"id":"7DTcMndyZHbx4jCTPhtzsB","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"advice_question_Rosita","title":"Any advice for those who are new to coding?","description":"Just start to learn, and learn at your own pace. Don't compare yourself to others, and take your time.\n"},{"id":"1DrCdyykvK7o7mDDl1BvNd","content_type":"titleDescription","internal_title":"fun_question_Rosita","title":"When you’re not coding, what do you do for fun?","description":"I love to cook, watch Netflix, and play The Sims 4.\n"}],"related_content":[{"id":"4nOq9vZR9JMSrjc6PAwFCp","content_type":"contentReference","type":"path","slug":"front-end-engineer-career-path"},{"id":"3eJrGvpyu19gVk3AMG9nBE","content_type":"contentReference","type":"course","slug":"learn-html"},{"id":"7XZceOk7HsZde5UwaFRC6","content_type":"contentReference","type":"category","slug":"javascript"},{"id":"7yYK7WBGgZxnmAU2bum7yt","content_type":"contentReference","type":"path","slug":"learn-how-to-build-websites"}]}]},"goals":[{"id":"6GI94gHYZDxvqNOt86wqN6","content_type":"goal","title":"Build a career","trac